news.title: Maharashtra government cancels all GRs related to redevelopment of Mhada buildings
news.para: All the GRs pertained to the requirement of a prior no-objection certificate from the state government for carrying out redevelopment.

news.title: OYO reports revenue at Rs 1,459 crore in April-June 2o22
news.para: For FY22, revenue from contract with customers was at Rs 4,781.4 crore. In FY21 it was at Rs 3,961.65 crore; Rs 13,168.15 crore in FY20 and Rs 6,329.74 crore in FY19, it added.

news.title: Protected Aravali land abuzz with construction, roads to borewells
news.para: This flurry of construction is underway in at least six sites at the Aravali Retreat in Raisina Hills, even though the land is protected under Section 4 of the Punjab Land Preservation Act (PLPA) as ‘gair mumkin pahar (uncultivable hill)’.

news.title: Gurugram civic body to file new plan for infrastructure in colonies by Sept 30
news.para: The tentative estimates for infrastructure augmentation were around Rs 8.5 crore for Sushant Lok 2, Rs 10 crore for Sushant Lok 3, Rs 8.5 crore for Ardee City and Rs 14 crore for Malibu Towne. However, these estimates will be revised.

news.title: MSEDCL starts cutting supply to Lavasa project over dues
news.para: An order from the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal dated September 2 had allowed the MSEDCL to terminate or suspend supply for non-payment of dues.

news.title: HDFC Capital raises over Rs 500 crore in first close of proptech fund
news.para: Through its initiative, HDFC Affordable Real Estate and Technology Program (HeART), it is looking to provide a platform to real estate technology companies with innovative products that would create competences and lower costs in each phase of the development cycle of a real estate project.

news.title: CBI files charge sheet against Rana Kapoor, Gautam Thapar in bank fraud case
news.para: In its charge sheet filed before the special CBI court in Mumbai, the probe agency has also named Thapar and Oyster Buildwell Pvt Ltd (OBPL) in the scam.

news.title: China Vanke's property services arm Onewo to raise $783 million through IPO
news.para: The subsidiary, Onewo Space-Tech Service, has set a price range of HK$47.1 to HK$52.7 a piece in the public offering of 116.74 million of its shares, which represent 10% of the company's share capital, according to a deal term sheet.

news.title: Eris Lifesciences’ CMD buys luxury apartment in Mumbai's Worli for Rs 61 crore
news.para: Bakshi has purchased the apartment spread over a carpet area of 64,50 sq ft on the 46th floor of the project from the developer, Oberoi Realty’s subsidiary Oasis Realty, that is executing the project.

news.title: DB Realty's subsidiary looks to sell Mumbai land for Rs 480 crore
news.para: Agreement for sale has not been been entered into. The proposed transaction is subject to customary diligence and necessary approvals and is expected to close within 60 to 90 days, it said.

news.title: Adani looks to become most profitable cement manufacturer
news.para: Stating reasons for the foray into the cement space, he said while India is the second largest producer of cement in the world, its per capita consumption is just 250 kg compared to 1,600 kg of China. "This is almost a 7x headroom for growth."

news.title: Ansal API under police lens for 'irregular' land deals in Panipat
news.para: The complaints have come from a group led by former district counsellor Jogender Swami, who alleged that the Ansal group and town planning department officials had connived in arranging the unlawful land deals.

news.title: Kanpur: KDA residency has no structural safety issues, say experts
news.para: ​​Rohit Khanna chief engineer KDA in a release stated that residents of the residency apartment had complained about structural safety.

news.title: Nagpur: Builder booked for cheating homebuyers of Rs 12.9 crore
news.para: ​Based on a complaint, the economic offences wing (EOW) of the police has registered a case against Shashank Govindprasad Pandey (46) under sections 406 (criminal breach of trust), 420 (cheating) and other relevant provisions of the Indian Penal Code.

news.title: Compensation, penalties cannot be taxed: Government
news.para: Chartered accountants, tax consultants and taxpayers were grappling over the question whether GST has to be paid for transactions such as liquidated damages, compensation, penalty, cancellation charges, late payment and penalties due to a breach of contract.
